anager<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, on the menu bar, choose                  <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>View<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>,                  <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Property Manager<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[19833,19971],"source":" To access                  **Property Manager**, on the menu bar, choose                  **View**,                  **Property Manager**."},{"content":"Property Manager shortcut menu","pos":[19980,20010]},{"content":"Under each configuration node, you see nodes for each property sheet that applies to that configuration.","pos":[20060,20164]},{"content":"The system adds property sheets that set values based on options you choose in the app wizard when you create the project.","pos":[20165,20287]},{"content":"Right-click any node and choose Properties to see the properties that apply to that node.","pos":[20288,20377]},{"content":"All the property sheets are imported automatically into the project's \"master\" property sheet (ms.cpp.props) and are evaluated in the order they appear in Property Manager.","pos":[20379,20551]},{"content":"You can move them to change the evaluation order.","pos":[20552,20601]},{"content":"Property sheets that are evaluated later will override the values in previously-evaluated sheets.","pos":[20602,20699]},{"content":"If you choose                  <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add New Project Property Sheet<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and then select, for example, the MyProps.props property sheet, a property page dialog box appears.","pos":[20706,20871],"source":"If you choose                  **Add New Project Property Sheet** and then select, for example, the MyProps.props property sheet, a property page dialog box appears."},{"content":"Notice that it applies to the MyProps property sheet; any changes you make are written to the sheet, not to the project file (.vcxproj).","pos":[20872,21008]},{"content":"Properties in a property sheet are overridden if the same property is set directly in the .vcxproj file.","pos